aight I've used that Jereome Russell Bblonde bleach kit before and tbh I wouldn't recommend it at all unless you have some strong ass hair, the only % you can get is 30 or 40 vol and it's so strong, I personally have really strong hair I can put through absolute hell but if you have any kind of delicate hair that stuff will cause your hair to break or fall out.
it's by no means bad because it does work it's just really really strong 😬

snippet.textDisplay: I had a bad hair thing happen. I regret it. Thankfully it's only last about like 10 washes. But basically I wanted to go blue. It's like my dream but everytime I use blue it's actually green. So here I am sitting in my washroom while my mom bleached my hair. And the she grabs our brush and started brushing it. I told her that she's not supposed to do that and that it's ridiculously painful and she just says oh well. And I have a really sensitive scalp so it was super painful. Ended out very choppy. When we washed it out she applied shampoo but no conditioner, so when i eent to vrush it. Well i couldnt brush it. Then we applied the dye and it was green out of the bottle. And we ran out cause i have super thick hair. SO now I have this choppy green and blue hair that looks terrible. So now I'm just waiting for the blue to come out. 😐

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm here just from freshly redoing my platinum blonde head with box dyes and ..... idk, my mother helps me with it and like, is getting a second person to help out and do the back the trick??? I've never had bad results, never burned my hair too badly (only ever fried some of it once many years ago, tbh) and I've been bleaching heavily for 9 yrs now.
...I don't like hairdressers, the thought of a stranger touching my hair is extremely uncomfortable to me, my mother dyes it, my friend cuts it, I'd rather risk bad results from myself and/or a person I trust than a stranger. Fortunately it's never been bad yet.

????? Why do so many of these people end up with disastrous hair ?????

6:54 so have I
I have albinism and it affects how my hair takes dye. I used splat semi-permanent dark purple that was supposed to wash out in 30 washes. Did it in June of 2019.
